www.vitac.com

03:16.850 --> 03:19.886
CAPTIONS PAID FOR BY
DISCOVERY COMMUNICATIONS

03:26.026 --> 03:30.531
[ SIGHS ]
I UNDERSTAND THAT.

03:30.531 --> 03:32.566
AND, UH...

03:36.236 --> 03:38.204
I FIND IT ADMIRABLE.

03:38.204 --> 03:42.876
BUT YOU MUST UNDERSTAND,
HANNA.

03:42.876 --> 03:45.512
WHAT IF IT WERE BENNY?

03:47.480 --> 03:53.453
THEN I WOULD HOLD HIS HAND
WHILE HE WENT ON TRIAL.

03:53.453 --> 03:58.525
IT'S EASY TO SAY
FROM THAT SIDE.

03:58.525 --> 04:01.702
EASY?

04:01.702 --> 04:05.872
NONE OF THIS IS EASY.

04:05.872 --> 04:08.909
MY SON IS STILL FIGHTING
FOR HIS LIFE.

04:12.112 --> 04:16.717
MRS. CRYER, I KNOW THAT
YOU STILL CARRY A LOT OF GUILT

04:16.717 --> 04:21.387
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED TO WYATT
WHEN HE WAS A BOY.

04:21.387 --> 04:25.992
BUT THIS IS JUST WRONG.

04:25.992 --> 04:30.997
NOW, YOU EXCUSE ME
FOR SAYING THIS,

04:30.997 --> 04:36.002
BUT YOU COVERING UP FOR YOUR SON
IS NOT THE BEST THING FOR HIM.

04:36.002 --> 04:40.340
YOU THINK THOSE DRUGS
WERE A PROBLEM BEFORE?

04:40.340 --> 04:42.643
YOU WAIT UNTIL
HE TRIES TO DEAL

04:42.643 --> 04:46.046
WITH THE GUILT OF THIS
WITHOUT ANY RESPONSIBILITY.

04:46.046 --> 04:49.249
YOU DON'T KNOW.

04:49.249 --> 04:51.384
I KNOW ENOUGH.

04:51.384 --> 04:54.454
NO, YOU DON'T.

04:54.454 --> 04:57.558
ARE YOU TELLING ME HE DIDN'T HIT
THAT LITTLE GIRL OR MY SON?

04:57.558 --> 05:02.235
[ SNIFFLES ] I'M TELLING YOU
THAT YOUR SON IS AT MERCY.

05:02.235 --> 05:05.706
YOU NEED TO ASK
FOR DR. BAYLOR.

05:08.108 --> 05:10.410
ANSWER ME, PLEASE.

05:17.851 --> 05:19.853
[ SNIFFLES ]

05:19.853 --> 05:22.656
YOUR SON IS AT MERCY.

05:22.656 --> 05:25.191
HE'S AT MERCY HOSPITAL.

05:28.428 --> 05:32.098
YES, OKAY.

05:32.098 --> 05:36.637
AND, AGAIN,
I THANK YOU FOR THAT.

05:36.637 --> 05:39.506
AND, AGAIN...

05:41.908 --> 05:44.444
I'M SORRY.

05:48.014 --> 05:50.250
SO AM I.

05:55.221 --> 05:56.890
KATHERYN.

05:56.890 --> 05:58.892
[ SNIFFLES, SIGHS ]
IS HE HERE YET?

05:58.892 --> 06:00.160
NO. HANNA.

06:00.160 --> 06:02.168
MR. CRYER.
SO, YOU DID THIS.

06:02.168 --> 06:03.537
I DIDN'T WANT TO.

06:03.537 --> 06:05.639
OH, YOU DIDN'T WANT TO, BUT YOU
SURE AS HELL DID, DIDN'T YOU?

06:05.639 --> 06:06.940
I DID WHAT I HAD TO DO.

06:06.940 --> 06:08.108
WHAT YOU HAD TO DO

06:08.108 --> 06:10.644
WAS NOT SAY A WORD TO ANYBODY
ABOUT ANYTHING.

06:10.644 --> 06:12.513
EXCUSE ME?
YOU MUST BE CRAZY.

06:12.513 --> 06:14.314
WHAT DID YOU
JUST SAY TO ME?

06:14.314 --> 06:15.849
YOU MUST BE CRAZY.

06:15.849 --> 06:17.183
I'M GONNA DO
EVERYTHING I CAN

06:17.183 --> 06:18.785
TO FORGET I EVER HEARD
YOU SAY THAT.

06:18.785 --> 06:20.220
JIM.
NO.

06:20.220 --> 06:22.989
SHE CAN'T TALK TO ME LIKE
THAT ‐‐ BEING DISRESPECTFUL.

06:22.989 --> 06:25.258
WELL, IT'S A GOOD THING I DON'T
WORK FOR YOU ANYMORE,
THEN, ISN'T IT?

06:25.258 --> 06:26.459
IT'S A VERY GOOD THING.

06:26.459 --> 06:28.394
YOU SAVED ME THE TROUBLE
OF HAVING TO FIRE YOUR ASS.

06:28.394 --> 06:29.730
ALL RIGHT, ENOUGH.

06:29.730 --> 06:31.397
I'VE HAD ENOUGH OF YOU, TOO,
KATHERYN.

06:31.397 --> 06:33.466
YOU'RE DEFENDING HER
AFTER SHE TURNED OUR SON IN?

06:33.466 --> 06:34.467
I KNOW THAT.

06:34.467 --> 06:35.836
SHE DOESN'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT SHE SAW.

06:35.836 --> 06:37.470
[ SIGHS ]
I HAVE TO GO.

06:37.470 --> 06:39.205
YEAH, YOU GO ON.

06:39.205 --> 06:41.508
BUT, YOU'RE WRONG, HANNA.
YOU ARE DEAD WRONG.

06:41.508 --> 06:43.710
NO, WHAT'S WRONG
IS YOU THREATENING ME

06:43.710 --> 06:46.179
AND YOU TRYING TO MAKE ME
THINK I WAS CRAZY.

06:46.179 --> 06:48.214
I KNOW WHAT I SAW,
AND I KNOW WHAT I HEARD!

06:48.214 --> 06:50.350
WHAT DID YOU HEAR, HANNA?
WHAT DID YOU HEAR?

06:50.350 --> 06:52.686
AS I TOLD YOU,
I HEARD WYATT SAY HE HIT SOMEONE

06:52.686 --> 06:54.688
AND THAT HE THOUGHT
HE HAD KILLED THEM.

06:54.688 --> 06:57.290
NOW, YOU ALL MAY BE ABLE
TO LIVE THIS WAY, BUT I CAN'T.

06:57.290 --> 06:59.059
I CAN'T WITH THE GUILT.
I'M SORRY.

06:59.059 --> 07:00.594
YOU'LL BE LIVING
WITH PLENTY OF GUILT

07:00.594 --> 07:02.569
WHEN YOU FIND OUT WHAT
REALLY HAPPENED, BELIEVE ME.

07:02.569 --> 07:03.704
WHAT?

07:03.704 --> 07:04.771
YOU HEARD ME.

07:04.771 --> 07:06.239
IS THAT ANOTHER THREAT,
MR. CRYER?

07:06.239 --> 07:08.341
'CAUSE I HAD A MAJOR PROBLEM
WITH IT THE FIRST TIME.

07:08.341 --> 07:09.943
YES. IT IS.

07:09.943 --> 07:12.312
JIM. STOP IT.

07:14.447 --> 07:17.117
YOU'LL SEE, HANNA.

07:17.117 --> 07:18.652
I HAVE TO GO CHECK
ON MY SON.

07:18.652 --> 07:20.086
I DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR THIS.

07:20.086 --> 07:22.022
WHAT?

07:22.022 --> 07:23.724
YES.

07:23.724 --> 07:25.759
CHECK ON YOUR SON?

07:25.759 --> 07:27.093
YES.

07:27.093 --> 07:28.862
MY SON IS ALIVE.

07:28.862 --> 07:29.863
WHAT?

07:29.863 --> 07:31.898
YES, HE'S ALIVE.

07:31.898 --> 07:34.400
I THOUGHT THAT YOUR ‐‐

07:34.400 --> 07:35.736
NO.

07:35.736 --> 07:37.938
AND JUST LIKE
ALL THE OTHER THINGS

07:37.938 --> 07:40.473
YOU THOUGHT ABOUT MY SON,
YOU WERE WRONG.

07:40.473 --> 07:43.977
WELL, JUST LIKE ALL THE THINGS
YOU THOUGHT ABOUT MY SON,

07:43.977 --> 07:45.812
YOU WERE WRONG.

07:45.812 --> 07:47.714
I KNOW WHAT I HEARD.

07:50.150 --> 07:53.554
AND THEN YOU JUST ASSUMED
THAT IT WAS HIM.

07:53.554 --> 07:57.290
IT ALL MAKES SENSE,
MR. CRYER.

07:57.290 --> 07:59.960
IF YOU SAY SO, HANNA.

07:59.960 --> 08:02.969
I KNOW SO.

08:02.969 --> 08:05.138
I HAVE TO GO.

08:05.138 --> 08:11.477
THANK YOU FOR GETTING ME OUT
AND FOR ALL YOU'VE DONE.

08:11.477 --> 08:13.814
SURE.

08:13.814 --> 08:15.949
HANNA, WHEN YOU FIND OUT
WHAT REALLY HAPPENED

08:15.949 --> 08:18.018
AND YOU COME CRAWLING BACK
FOR FORGIVENESS,

08:18.018 --> 08:20.954
KATHERYN MAY FORGIVE YOU,
BUT I SURE AS HELL WON'T.

08:31.364 --> 08:33.499
WHAT THE HELL
WAS SHE DOING HERE?

08:33.499 --> 08:35.001
FIELDMAN
HAD HER ARRESTED.

08:35.001 --> 08:36.369
FOR WHAT?
I DON'T KNOW.

08:36.369 --> 08:37.538
SOME FAMILY COURT MATTER.

08:37.538 --> 08:38.872
WHAT KIND
OF A FAMILY COURT MATTER?

08:38.872 --> 08:40.641
JIM, DO WE REALLY HAVE TIME
TO BE TALKING ABOUT HER?

08:40.641 --> 08:42.175
AND WHAT WAS SHE DOING
TALKING ABOUT HER SON?

08:42.175 --> 08:43.309
WHAT WAS THAT?

08:43.309 --> 08:44.678
WHAT ABOUT HIM?

08:44.678 --> 08:46.680
SHE WAS TALKING ABOUT HER SON,
KATHERYN.

08:46.680 --> 08:48.649
WHAT WAS THAT ABOUT?
YOU HEARD HER.

08:48.649 --> 08:49.683
HE'S ALIVE.

08:51.952 --> 08:53.720
KATHERYN.
WHAT?

08:53.720 --> 08:56.056
WHAT DID YOU DO?

08:56.056 --> 08:57.824
I HAD HIM MOVED.

09:00.060 --> 09:03.737
AFTER I EXPLICITLY TOLD YOU
NOT TO?

09:03.737 --> 09:04.738
YES.

09:04.738 --> 09:06.139
YOU NEVER LISTEN TO ME.

09:06.139 --> 09:08.642
[ SCOFFS ]
WELL, ON THAT WE CAN AGREE.

09:08.642 --> 09:10.544
BUT I DIDN'T WANT HIM
TO DIE.

09:10.544 --> 09:12.478
SO, YOU HAD HER SON MOVED,

09:12.478 --> 09:15.916
AND SHE GOES RIGHT AHEAD
AND TURNS IN OUR SON.

09:15.916 --> 09:17.818
DO YOU EVEN HEAR YOURSELF?

09:17.818 --> 09:19.085
I DID WHAT WAS RIGHT.

09:19.085 --> 09:21.421
YOU DID WHAT WAS STUPID.

09:21.421 --> 09:24.825
KATHERYN, WHAT IS RIGHT IS
NOT GETTING ANY MORE INVOLVED

09:24.825 --> 09:26.893
IN THIS THING
THAN YOU HAVE TO.

09:26.893 --> 09:28.695
SHE'S GOING TO SUE US,
KATHERYN.

09:28.695 --> 09:30.897
YOU UNDERSTAND THAT
AT ALL?

09:30.897 --> 09:32.566
AND NOW, THANKS TO YOU,

09:32.566 --> 09:35.401
SHE HAS ALL THE TOOLS
SHE NEEDS TO SUCCEED.

09:35.401 --> 09:38.104
HOW DO YOU THINK IT'S GONNA
SOUND IN AN OPEN COURT,

09:38.104 --> 09:39.740
YOU TRYING
TO HELP HER SON?

09:39.740 --> 09:42.843
IT WILL SOUND LIKE I TRIED
TO HELP HER SAVE HIM.

09:42.843 --> 09:44.645
NO, IT WILL SOUND
LIKE YOU'RE TRYING

09:44.645 --> 09:46.880
TO BUY HER SILENCE ‐‐
SIMPLE.

09:46.880 --> 09:50.350
JIM, YOU KNOW IN YOUR HEART
THIS IS FOR THE BEST.

09:50.350 --> 09:52.352
NO, KATHERYN, IT'S NOT.

09:52.352 --> 09:54.187
YOU ARE MAKING IT WORSE.

09:54.187 --> 09:55.288
YOU NEED TO STOP.

09:55.288 --> 09:56.557
IF HER SON DIES,

09:56.557 --> 09:58.659
WYATT IS LOOKING
AT A DOUBLE HOMICIDE.

09:58.659 --> 10:00.794
HAVE YOU THOUGHT ABOUT,
JUDGE CRYER?

10:00.794 --> 10:03.303
[ STAMMERS ]
BE QUIET. OKAY?

10:03.303 --> 10:05.305
SHE'S A PROBLEM.

10:05.305 --> 10:07.340
SHE WENT TO THE POLICE.

10:07.340 --> 10:09.142
AND I CAN'T BLAME HER.

10:10.911 --> 10:12.112
WHAT?

10:15.115 --> 10:17.618
MAYBE THIS IS
FOR THE BEST.

10:17.618 --> 10:20.053
WHAT IN THE HELL
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

10:20.053 --> 10:21.855
HE DID IT, JIM.

10:21.855 --> 10:24.024
KATHERYN.
HE DID.

10:24.024 --> 10:26.359
[ STAMMERS,
CHUCKLES INCREDULOUSLY ]

10:26.359 --> 10:30.697
You need to quiet
in this room, okay?

10:30.697 --> 10:32.198
Cameras, Katheryn.

10:32.198 --> 10:35.702
OUR SON HAS A DRUG PROBLEM,
AND HE KILLED ‐‐

10:35.702 --> 10:38.304
[ Sternly ] KATHERYN CRYER,
THIS IS YOUR LAST WARNING.

10:44.077 --> 10:45.846
MAYBE WE SHOULD
JUST LET HIM PAY FOR THIS.

10:45.846 --> 10:47.848
OH, FOR CRYING OUT LOUD,
ARE YOU NOT HEARING ME?

10:47.848 --> 10:49.382
WE HAVE ALWAYS BEEN
PROTECTING HIM.

10:49.382 --> 10:51.184
ARE YOU NOT HEARING ME?
CAMERAS, KATHERYN.

10:51.184 --> 10:52.853
POLICE STATION, KATHERYN.

10:52.853 --> 10:56.189
EARS LISTENING, KATHERYN.

10:56.189 --> 10:58.792
THIS IS NOT THE TIME
OR THE PLACE

10:58.792 --> 11:01.267
TO BE HAVING
THIS CONVERSATION.

11:01.267 --> 11:03.269
THIS IS GONNA DESTROY HIM.

11:03.269 --> 11:06.339
I ‐‐ [ SIGHS ]
I KNOW THAT.

11:06.339 --> 11:08.609
THAT'S WHY I'VE ALREADY
TAKEN CARE OF IT.

11:08.609 --> 11:10.076
HOW HAVE YOU HANDLED IT?

11:10.076 --> 11:12.546
IF YOU WOULD SIT HERE AND ACT
LIKE THE CONCERNED PARENT,

11:12.546 --> 11:14.915
MAYBE YOU WOULD FIND OUT.

11:21.354 --> 11:23.056
MAYBE WE SHOULD LET HIM PAY
FOR THIS.

11:23.056 --> 11:24.390
[ SIGHS ]

11:24.390 --> 11:26.593
WE HAVE ALWAYS BEEN
PROTECTING HIM.

11:26.593 --> 11:28.595
[ Sternly ] KATHERYN.

11:28.595 --> 11:31.431
STOP IT.

11:31.431 --> 11:34.434
STOP IT.

11:34.434 --> 11:37.771
WHY DON'T YOU JUST GO HOME?
LET ME HANDLE THIS.

11:37.771 --> 11:40.173
A BABY, JIM?
NO, NO.

11:40.173 --> 11:41.608
WITH THAT WHORE?

11:41.608 --> 11:43.577
NO, I'M NOT GONNA HAVE THIS ‐‐
I WILL NOT SIT HERE ‐‐

11:43.577 --> 11:45.111
I'M NOT GOING TO HAVE
THIS CONVERSATION

11:45.111 --> 11:47.781
IN A POLICE WAITING ROOM,
OKAY?

11:47.781 --> 11:49.516
I UNDERSTAND.
YOU'RE UPSET WITH ME.

11:49.516 --> 11:51.585
YOU'RE ALWAYS UPSET WITH ME.
I'M USED TO IT.

11:51.585 --> 11:53.419
BUT YOU CANNOT HANG OUR SON
OUT TO DRY

11:53.419 --> 11:56.089
BECAUSE YOU'RE MAD AT ME.

11:56.089 --> 11:59.025
WHY DON'T YOU GO TO HELL.

11:59.025 --> 12:00.861
I DON'T NEED TO GO TO HELL.
I LIVE IN HELL.

12:00.861 --> 12:03.203
I'M MARRIED TO THE DEVIL,
REMEMBER?

12:03.203 --> 12:06.673
OH, I'LL SHOW YOU
THE DEVIL.

12:10.243 --> 12:11.578
[ MUTTERS ]

12:20.754 --> 12:23.423
CAN YOU BELIEVE
THAT CANDACE GIRL?

12:23.423 --> 12:25.926
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]
I KNOW.

12:25.926 --> 12:27.694
SHOWING UP LIKE THAT?

12:27.694 --> 12:30.096
I KNOW.

12:30.096 --> 12:33.266
DO YOU ALSO KNOW
SHE'S GONNA BE A PROBLEM

12:33.266 --> 12:34.801
FOR THIS ENTIRE CAMPAIGN?

12:34.801 --> 12:36.803
I KNOW.

12:36.803 --> 12:38.404
WE ARE HANDLING IT.

12:38.404 --> 12:40.741
HMM.

12:40.741 --> 12:42.408
SO AM I.

12:42.408 --> 12:44.578
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

12:44.578 --> 12:48.281
IT MEANS I HAVE AN IRON
IN THE FRYER MYSELF.

12:50.283 --> 12:51.952
VERONICA.

12:51.952 --> 12:53.419
WHAT?

12:53.419 --> 12:54.921
WHAT ARE YOU UP TO?

12:54.921 --> 12:58.725
JUST DOING WHAT
A WOMAN USUALLY HAS TO DO.

12:58.725 --> 13:01.267
ALL RIGHT,
AND WHAT IS THAT, EXACTLY?

13:01.267 --> 13:04.938
CLEAN UP A MAN'S MESS.

13:04.938 --> 13:08.274
I WANT TO KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE UP TO.

13:08.274 --> 13:11.011
I WANT TO KNOW
WHERE JIM WAS RUNNING OFF TO.

13:11.011 --> 13:13.279
I HAVE NO IDEA.
[ SIGHS ]

13:13.279 --> 13:16.550
PROBABLY GOING TO MEET HER
IN A HOTEL ROOM.

13:16.550 --> 13:19.553
MM. A BABY?

13:19.553 --> 13:22.556
[ SIGHS ]

13:22.556 --> 13:24.558
IF I WERE KATHERYN,

13:24.558 --> 13:27.728
I WOULD CUT OFF HIS BALLS
AND HAND THEM TO HIM.

13:27.728 --> 13:31.197
WELL, THEY'RE BOTH OUR FRIENDS,
SO LET'S NOT ‐‐

13:31.197 --> 13:32.799
I DON'T LIKE HIM.

13:32.799 --> 13:34.467
THAT IS OBVIOUS.

13:34.467 --> 13:36.302
I MEAN, I USED TO.

13:36.302 --> 13:40.306
YOU KNOW
I GENUINELY DID LIKE HIM.

13:40.306 --> 13:43.009
BUT, UGH,
HE'S BECOME SUCH AN ASS.

13:43.009 --> 13:44.678
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:44.678 --> 13:47.681
[ Chuckling ] I GUESS
HE'S ALWAYS BEEN AN ASS.

13:47.681 --> 13:51.351
BUT NOW HIS ARROGANCE,
IT'S ‐‐ UGH.

13:51.351 --> 13:53.520
IT'S APPALLING.

13:53.520 --> 13:58.258
WELL, JIM AND I ARE CONNECTED
AT THE HIP FOR AWHILE.

13:58.258 --> 14:00.426
UNFORTUNATELY.

14:00.426 --> 14:02.168
[ SIGHS ]

14:06.206 --> 14:08.575
SHALL WE TALK ABOUT
WHAT ELSE IS APPALLING?

14:08.575 --> 14:12.012
WHAT WOULD THAT BE?

14:12.012 --> 14:15.448
JEFFERY BEING PUSHED
INTO TALKING TO THAT GIRL.

14:15.448 --> 14:19.085
MM. I KNOW. I DIDN'T WANT HIM
TALKING TO HER, EITHER.

14:21.087 --> 14:22.923
YOU DIDN'T?

14:22.923 --> 14:24.290
NO.

14:24.290 --> 14:28.461
HUH. GOOD.

14:28.461 --> 14:31.431
HAPPY TO SEE
YOU'RE COMING AROUND.

14:31.431 --> 14:32.933
HMM.

14:32.933 --> 14:36.336
I WANT HIM TO BE
WITH A BLACK GIRL, DAVID.

14:36.336 --> 14:39.405
